        <main id="main" class="main" role="main">
        <section id="collection-mujib-mashal" class="mujib-mashal-collection collection" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/CollectionPage">
        <header class="collection-header">
        <div class="collection-meta">
            <div class="collection-meta-header">
    <div class="supported-by nocontent robots-nocontent hidden">
    <span class="ad-label">Supported by</span>
    <div id="SupportedBy" class="supported-by-ad ad"></div>
</div>    <h3 class="kicker">
        <span class="kicker-label">
            <a href=""></a>
        </span>
            </h3>
</div><!-- close collection-meta-header -->
            <div class="collection-meta-group">

                                <div class="collection-image">
                    <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/10/15/multimedia/author-mujib-mashal/author-mujib-mashal-thumbLarge.png" />
                </div>
                
                <div class="collection-headings">

    <div class="collection-heading-group">

                                 
            <h1 class="collection-heading" itemprop="name">
                Mujib Mashal            </h1>
                                        <div class="follow-button-placeholder" style="" data-collection-id="byline.mujib-mashal"></div>
                    
            </div><!-- close collection-heading-group -->

    
    
            <h2 class="collection-subheading" itemprop="about">Mujib Mashal is The New York Times senior correspondent in Afghanistan. Before joining the paper, he wrote for magazines such as The Atlantic, Harper’s, Time and others.                        <a class="user-action">More<i class="icon caret-icon"></i></a>
                    </h2>
    
    
</div><!-- close collection-headings -->

            </div>
        </div>
            </header>
            <div class="collection-description">
        <p>Mujib Mashal is The New York Times senior correspondent in Afghanistan. Before joining the paper, he wrote for magazines such as The Atlantic, Harper&#8217;s, Time and others.</p>
<p>He began his journalism career as an intern with The Times&#8217;s bureau in Kabul, Afghanistan, in 2010, before moving on to work for Al Jazeera English in Doha and then pursue magazine writing. He returned to The Times as a senior correspondent in October 2016. Born in Kabul, he received a degree in history from Columbia University.</p>    </div>
    
    

    
